	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65476868"><p>Section 230 is part of Title 47 (Telecommunications) of the U.S. Code.  It has nothing to do with copyright, which is covered by Title 17.</p><p>If you want to consider copyright cases in the context of the Internet we could look at Metallica v. Napster Inc, which<nobr> <wbr></nobr>... led to no changes to the law after it became clear that Napster would have to settle or lose.</p><p>Or we could consider Viacom International Inc. v. YouTube, Inc., which<nobr> <wbr></nobr>... led to no changes in the law after YouTube lost an appeal and settled the case rat<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

