	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65477290">It's not a question as to whether or not a copy was made. Absolutely a copy was made. The act of training <b>requires</b> copies be made.<br>
The question is whether or not those copies are covered under fair use. If they are transformative, and not proven to have a negative market impact on the copyright holder- then they are.<br>
<br>
The Judge is not wrong, they know the law better than you, and the dumbshits who positively moderated you.<br>
<br>
Also, the CDA has <b>literally nothing</b> to do with copyright.<br>
Copyright law is Title 17</div>
	</div>

