		<div id="comment_body_65478032"><p>The failure to litigate was expected.</p><p>I wonder if there are any lawyers who bother to learn about the technology first, because when you read the lawsuits, it often seems as if you wouldn't need a lawyer at all. You could refute the claims simply by presenting the neural network's diagram, which shows the technical impossibility of the assertions. Of course, you'd still need a lawyer to translate the technical details into language a judge can comprehend.</p><p>Have you read the court documents from the Andersen ca<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
